item.title: 261. Race To Berlin 1945: A Devastated City Divided (Ep 1)
item.description: What was life like in Berlin in the immediate aftermath of the Second World War? Why did the Red Army steal taps from Berlin houses when they reached the city? Was the famous photo of the red flag on the Reichstag staged or authentic? Anita and William are joined by Giles Milton, author of Checkmate in Berlin: The Cold War Showdown That Shaped the Modern World, to discuss the division and destitution of the capital city after the Second World War... Feed: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/empirepodcast
